<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Character Transfer Petition</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=62155" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abm.asp?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    Received from Apocalypseious. You can also chat this in Forums: <a href="http://www.everlore.com/boards/EL/Forum1/HTML/001466.html">Character Transfer Petition</a>
<blockquote>
<p>
Hello all, my name is Apocalypseious and am a member of good standing in Regulators of Norrath on the Eci Server.  I come to you today with hopes that what I have to say in this petition will pass in an optional patch format.</p>
<p> 
Have you ever thought of creating a new account and transferring a character of yours from one account to the other? Well I know I have, for many reasons which I will get into later, and I know my friends have to, but the sad thing is- we cannot.  We as Everquest Hard-core Players paying $10 a month in fees do not have the ability to take a character and transfer it on to another account, not even on the same server.  Now most of you are thinking, 
"What is the purpose of transferring characters into different accounts Apoc?"</p>
<p>
Well I am glad you asked.
Have you ever wanted to play with your brother, sister or best friend and let them use one of your characters while you are playing on one on another computer?
Well you can't.</p>
<p>
You cannot have more than one person logged in an account.
So you think,</p>
<p>
"No problem, I can just create another account and transfer the character to it, on the same server of course, and I can play with them on another account."
Well you can't do that either.
Here is another example that I bet most of us have gone through.
A family member created a character, on your account of course, and like all of us, got addicted.  This family member is playing their character for the duration of time our local 7-11 is open.  This would, of course, result to less, if any, time spent on your character resulting to HAVOC!  If we were allowed to create another account and be able to transfer that family members character into it, it will bring relief to all those hard-core EQ players who were going through withdrawal due to the lack of play time.</p>
<p>
If you want to give your best friend or co-worker a character you started for them by putting it into another account for you or both of you to play whenever you wish, you should be able to.
Now it maybe hard or difficult to transfer a character from one server to another, but creating two accounts and having them both on a server for your friends and family to play while you are in your own account, should not be overlooked.</p>
<p> 
I do believe it is the gamers choice however to have this option or not, so I am not looking for a mandatory patch, just an optional patch that we rarely use anyways.</p>
<p>
I have brought up this issue to you today because I have a great deal of respect for the makers of EQ and the game itself, it has changed the say we look at Online RPG, I just hope that now that I have brought this issue/topic up to all of you, that maybe you fell the same way too and want to do something about it.  If you do feel this way, then join myself and members of Regulators of Norrath send emails to Verant through the official <a href="http://www.everquest.com">Everquest Website</a> and tell them that you think this is a good idea.</p>
<p>
Remember, we will only get this passed in numbers, not thoughts or wishful thinking that this will resolve itself.</p>
<p>
Take care and if you see me on Eci, and can spell my name, tell me how you feel about this issue.</p>
<p>
Sincerely,<br>
Apocalypseious<br>
22 Shm<br>
Regulators of Norrath<br>
Eci</p>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
